        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-06T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-06T13:00:00-05:00" n="337" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d337">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.24/10–647: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Flack</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-06T14:00:00-04:00">October 6, 1947—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>863. Renegotiation Lend-Lease has been rather delicate, but Sub-secretary told me
                    today enabling decree was signed by President and Cabinet October 3. He will
                    make early appointment for meeting with Finance Minister, Guachalla,<note n="2" xml:id="d337fn1">Carlos Guachalla.</note> to determine essential details of
                    initial payment into bank here.</p>
                <p>Subsecretary assured me on Saturday and today (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 532, October 3) Bolivian Government will meet our wishes
                    avoidance publicity specific figures re amount received by Bolivia and amount
                    due, limiting itself in official announcement to statement like “a payment was
                    made to United States on Lend-Lease obligations”. He said Cabinet and some
                    senators had necessarily been informed, but they would regard matter as
                    officially confidential.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Flack</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
